FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774576986
OL,3,CStarmer: I'm not going anywhere and
OL,4,CRayner has a lot to offer
OL,6,FSir Keir sought to manage expectations
OL,7,Fahead of the local polls this spring,
OL,8,Fdescribing them as "very much sort of
OL,9,Fmid-term elections" of the kind that
OL,10,Fincumbent governments historically
OL,11,F"pretty well lose".
OL,13,FBut asked whether he was "going
OL,14,Fanywhere," he said: "No. I intend to
OL,15,Fbe judged at the next election on what
OL,16,FI've delivered for the country."
OL,26,@pD@TOUqD@SO]sD@AOUsD@RO]uD@ZOUvD@JO]vD@
OL,26,AUOUxD@`O]
