OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1774576986
OL,3,CStarmer: I'm not going anywhere and
OL,4,CRayner has a lot to offer
OL,6,FIn a speech last week, Ms Rayner had
OL,7,Fappeared to highlight a particular
OL,8,Fconcern over Government proposals to
OL,9,Fdouble the time it will take to
OL,10,Fqualify for indefinite leave to remain
OL,11,F(ILR) from five to 10 years and its
OL,12,Fimplications for people already in the
OL,13,FUK.
OL,15,FMinisters have said debates are
OL,16,Fwelcome in the Labour Party and
OL,17,FDowning Street has said the plans are
OL,18,Fbeing consulted on, with a Government
OL,19,Fresponse to be set out in "due course."
OL,26,@{D@[OU{D@gO]
